<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
A student stands on a deck near the top of a lighthouse at the coast of Mombasa. The student's eyes are <alert><m>{3}</m> m</alert> above the deck floor shown in the diagram. The student looks down at a buoy floating on the sea. The angle of depression to the buoy is <alert><m>{30}</m>°</alert>. The horizontal distance from the base of the lighthouse to the buoy is <alert><m>{16}</m> m</alert>.
</p>

<p>
Find the total height of the lighthouse above sea level.
</p>

<div style="margin:10px 0;">
<svg width="520" height="300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">

  <!-- Sea level / ground -->
  <line x1="55" y1="225" x2="405" y2="225" stroke="black" stroke-width="2"/>

  <!-- Viewing platform vertical -->
  <line x1="95" y1="225" x2="95" y2="75" stroke="black" stroke-width="2"/>

  <!-- Deck floor -->
  <line x1="95" y1="140" x2="145" y2="140" stroke="black" stroke-width="2"/>

  <!-- Eye-above-deck segment -->
  <line x1="145" y1="140" x2="145" y2="115" stroke="black" stroke-width="1.5"/>

  <!-- Eye point -->
  <circle cx="145" cy="115" r="3" fill="black"/>

  <!-- Horizontal through eye -->
  <line x1="145" y1="115" x2="280" y2="115" stroke="black" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="6,4"/>

  <!-- Line of sight -->
  <line x1="145" y1="115" x2="330" y2="225" stroke="black" stroke-width="2"/>

  <!-- Right angle marker -->
  <path d="M95 210 L108 210 L108 225" fill="none" stroke="black" stroke-width="1.5"/>

  <!-- Angle arc -->
  <path d="M165 115 A22 22 0 0 1 158 131" fill="none" stroke="black" stroke-width="1.5"/>

  <!-- Labels near the top -->
  <text x="150" y="110" font-size="14">eye</text>
  <text x="118" y="128" font-size="15"><m>{3}</m> m</text>
  <text x="170" y="129" font-size="15"><m>{30}</m>°</text>

  <!-- Left-side label -->
  <text x="18" y="155" font-size="15">height = ?</text>

  <!-- Deck label -->
  <text x="120" y="156" font-size="13">deck</text>

  <!-- Bottom labels -->
  <text x="210" y="245" font-size="15"><m>{16}</m> m</text>
  <text x="316" y="244" font-size="14">buoy</text>
  <text x="336" y="214" font-size="13">sea level</text>

</svg>
</div>

<p>
Distance = <fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/> <alert>m</alert>  
</p>

<p>
Give your answer correct to <alert>1 decimal place</alert>.
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the right triangle.
</p>

<p>
The angle of depression is measured from the horizontal through the student's eye.
The horizontal distance is <m>{16}</m> m.
The unknown vertical drop from the eye to the sea is the opposite side.
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Use tangent.
</p>

<p>
<me>
\tan({30}^\circ)=\frac{\text{vertical drop}}{16}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Let the vertical drop be <m>x</m>.
Then
<me>
x={16}\tan({30}^\circ)
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
x \approx {9.2}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Add the eye height above the deck.
</p>

<p>
The total height of the lighthouse is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\text{height} = x + {3}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
\text{height} \approx {9.2} + {3} = {12.2}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the total height of the lighthouse above sea level is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\boxed{12.2} \text{ m}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>12.2</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>